descript.abstract: This polygon shows the standard 3 mile California state water boundary. It was created by buffering the line file called county-coast.shp, a generalized CA state boundary. This polygon does not account for the addition area of state water created as a result of offshore rocks or mounts, see especially in the northern part of California. This file has been found to not appropriatly represent the 3 nautical mile boundary as rendered on NOAA nautical charts. Statewaters_noaa.shp has been created to used for representation of political boundary.
descript.purpose: To show a 3 mile buffer of the California Coast.
descript.supplinf:
Converted to California Teale Albers NAD83 by the California Department of Fish and Game
This line is to be use for approximations only and is not considered a legaly binding boundary. DO NOT USE this file for representation of California's jurisdiction of ocean waters.
